# This file ensures the photos directory is tracked in git
# Add your photo files (.jpg, .jpeg, .png, .bmp, .gif, .tiff, .tif, .webp) to this directory
# The photo-album board will randomly select one when run
# 
# To use the photo album board:
# 1. Add your image files (.jpg, .jpeg, .png, .bmp, .gif, .tiff, .webp) to this directory
# 2. Run: python3 photo-album.py (without arguments to select random photo)
# 3. Or: python3 photo-album.py path/to/specific/image.jpg
#
# Supported options:
# --pad                    : Pad image to fit screen while maintaining aspect ratio
# --background-color COLOR : Background color for padding (default: white) 